modules.description: This module provides functions to bind and listen on a network socket for DNS server operations, process DNS packets using zone data, and serve DNS responses from zone files or buffers. It works with file descriptors, socket addresses, DNS packets, and zone data structures. Concrete use cases include setting up a DNS server that responds to queries based on predefined zone data, either loaded from files or in-memory buffers.

This module implements DNS resolution using a configurable client and server setup, supporting standard queries like name-to-IP and IP-to-name lookups. It works with IP addresses, DNS packets, and domain names, handling both forward and reverse DNS queries. It is used to perform low-level DNS resolution in Unix environments, such as resolving hostnames during network connection setup or validating DNS records.
